        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 5:54PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 553 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 7 miles south of Devers, or 10 miles southwest of Nome,
moving southwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mont Belvieu, Anahuac, Old River-Winfree, Ames, Cove, Devers,
Hankamer, and Wallisville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
